{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Sweet and sour sauce","content":["Place sugar, vinegar, soy sauce, tomato sauce, pineapple juice and cornflour into mixing bowl and cook <b>5 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside. Do not clean mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Spring rolls","content":["Place cabbage and coriander (optional) into mixing bowl and chop <b>2 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer into a large bowl and set aside.","Place ginger and garlic into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>.","Add mushrooms, spring onions\/shallots, water chestnuts and carrots and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer into bowl with cabbage and stir well to combine.","Place sesame oil into mixing bowl and heat <b>2 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>.","Add mince, prawns, soy sauce, salt, pepper and cornflour. Stir with aid of spatula, then sauté <b>2 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>. Transfer into bowl with chopped vegetables and stir to combine.","Place 1 spring roll pastry sheet on a clean work surface with 1 corner facing you (in a diamond shape). Place 2 tablespoons of the filling in top corner of pastry sheet. Roll pastry over until it covers the filling; fold side corners in to create a roll (approx. 12-14 cm wide), then continue rolling to the bottom corner and seal. If needed, brush a little water on the edge to help seal the ends. Transfer onto a large plate and repeat with remaining pastry sheets and filling.","Place a deep saucepan over high heat and fill three-quarters full with oil. Working in batches, brush spring rolls with egg wash and carefully place into hot oil. Fry for  3-5 minutes or until golden all over. Using a slotted spoon, carefully remove from oil and drain on paper towels. Serve hot with reserved Sweet and sour sauce."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Sweet and sour sauce","content":["60 g white sugar","2 tbsp rice wine vinegar","1 tbsp soy sauce","1 tbsp tomato sauce","100 g pineapple juice","1 tsp cornflour"]},{"title":"Spring rolls","content":["200 g cabbage, cut in pieces","3 - 5 sprigs fresh coriander, to taste (optional)","3 cm piece fresh ginger, peeled","2 garlic cloves","20 g dried shiitake mushroom, cut into slices","150 g spring onions\/shallots, trimmed and cut in pieces","12 canned water chestnuts, cut into halves","150 g carrot, cut into pieces","50 g sesame oil","100 g pork mince","100 g peeled raw prawns, deveined and roughly chopped","2 tbsp soy sauce","2 pinches salt","2 pinches ground white pepper","2 tsp cornflour","20 spring roll pastry sheets (see Tips)","water, for sealing","oil, for frying","1 egg, beaten"]}],"id":"r314184","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-b4_zB_JaQKk\/XZaeOkhoLnI\/AAAAAAAAgkA\/rul8SSPMOg0mYh812RabQSb3e8ol7oi4ACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_SHUOXM_ADWeNNRPL.png","title":"Prawn spring rolls with sweet and sour sauce","publishedAt":"2018-07-05T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{},"usefulItems":"paper towel, pastry brush, deep medium-sized saucepan, large bowl, bowl, large plate, slotted spoon, stove top","hintsAndTricks":["You can find spring roll pastry sheets in the frozen food aisle of most major supermarkets or from Asian food stores. Ensure that you purchase spring roll pastry sheets; rice vermicelli sheets will not work in this recipe."],"basicInfo":["medium","1h","1h 20m","20 portions"]}